---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="About - mcp-tool-shop"
  description="What mcp-tool-shop is building and why."
  currentPath="/about/"
>
  <div class="page-content">
    <h1>About</h1>
    <p>
      mcp-tool-shop builds MCP servers, desktop apps, and AI infrastructure.
      Everything runs locally. No cloud dependencies for core functionality.
    </p>

    <h2>Philosophy</h2>
    <p>
      Tools compose through the Model Context Protocol. Append-only where it matters.
      Accessibility baked in, not bolted on.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Local-first:</strong> Your data stays on your machine. Every tool works offline.</li>
      <li><strong>Composable:</strong> MCP-native from day one. Tools talk to each other through a shared protocol.</li>
      <li><strong>Deterministic:</strong> Same input, same output. No hidden randomness in critical paths.</li>
      <li><strong>Windows-first:</strong> Built and tested on Windows. Linux and macOS supported where applicable.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Stack</h2>
    <ul class="stack-list">
      <li><span class="tag">Python</span></li>
      <li><span class="tag">TypeScript</span></li>
      <li><span class="tag">C#</span></li>
      <li><span class="tag">.NET MAUI</span></li>
      <li><span class="tag">WinUI 3</span></li>
      <li><span class="tag">MCP</span></li>
      <li><span class="tag">FastMCP</span></li>
      <li><span class="tag">Ollama</span></li>
      <li><span class="tag">HNSW</span></li>
      <li><span class="tag">CUDA</span></li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Who</h2>
    <p>
      One developer, shipping tools under the
      <a href="https://github.com/mcp-tool-shop-org" rel="noopener">mcp-tool-shop-org</a>
      GitHub organization. All code is open source.
    </p>
  </div>
</Base>
